Building Automated Remediation Systems

Remediation Automation Levels

Level Description Human Involvement Risk Level
Level 1 Automated Detection & Alerting Manual remediation Low
Level 2 Suggested Remediation Approval required Low
Level 3 Conditional Auto-Remediation Pre-approved actions Medium

AI Remediation Best Practices

  1. Risk-Based Prioritization: AI-powered CVSS scoring and business impact
  2. Staged Rollout: Test environments before production
  3. Rollback Capabilities: Automated recovery from failed patches
  4. Change Management: Integration with ITSM workflows
  5. Compliance Tracking: Automated audit trails and reporting
  6. Testing Automation: Validate patches don't break functionality

Case Study: Netflix's Auto-Remediation

Netflix's security team built an AI system that automatically patches 95% of vulnerabilities without human intervention. Their system analyzes vulnerability impact, tests patches in staging, and rolls out fixes with automated rollback capabilities, reducing MTTR from weeks to hours.
